HEADWORD: noncurrent
<hw>noncurrent</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Not current or belonging to the
present time. Opposite of <ant>current</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms:
<stype>back(prenominal), out-of-date</stype>; <stype>discontinued, out
of print(predicate), out of production(predicate), out of
use(predicate)</stype>; <stype>disused, obsolete </stype>;
<stype>obsolete, outdated, outmoded, out-of-date, superannuated
</stype>; <stype>obsolescent </stype>] <see>Also See: <er>old</er>,
<er>past</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

